      "instructions": "Mix flour, chili powder, thyme, salt and pepper together on a large plate or tray.Heat oil and butter in a large skillet over medium heat until melted.  Swirl to combine.Dredge both sides of the fillets in the flour mixture to coat, shaking off any excess flour.  Cook in butter and oil for approximately 2-1/2 minutes or until flour is well browned.  Carefully flip fillets.  Add garlic to the skillet and shake to ensure that all garlic is immersed in oil-butter mixture.Cook fish an additional 2 minutes and remove pan from heat. Remove fish from skillet and arrange on serving plate.  Add remaining butter to skillet and stir to combine.  Ladle 1/2 of the sauce over each piece of fish and garnish with parsley if desired.Serve Immediately.Share and enjoy.",
